      "message": "Yeah, still is a pun... same value index is tracked all the way through.\n\nThe main reason I went with this instead of a memcpy() is that it keeps the constructor discipline of I32/F32 sane... the choices are\n\n    * init with NA                  --- obviously won\u0027t work here\n    * init with an immediate        --- only possible if x is an immediate\n    * init with any resolved value  --- yep, that\u0027s this.\n\nadd(), mul(), etc. all do the same thing, using id() to resolve any immediates on entry.\n\nid(x) is a logical no-op, and a literal actual no-op unless x is an immediate.",
